**[1840, 08-24] Ms.A.1.2.9.98.**

Pugh, Sarah, to RDW, Richard Allen, & James Haughton. [Liverpool].
Arrived safely ... enjoyed the opportunity “of mingling with those
interested in human beings...”

“Our passages are secured – and it is probable that tomorrow we shall
take our departure from the land on which three months since we landed –
with so much of joyful anticipation. That all we hoped for has been
realized we cannot say – yet that we have gained much more than we dared
to expect is also true – Amongst our highest pleasures we place the
opportunities enjoyed of mingling with those interested in {u}human
beings{/u} however degraded by circumstances – The consciousness that
this intercourse need not cease though an Ocean divide us is a great
consolation.


